  "commentary": "With SPX at 6763 sitting above the massive negative gamma wall at 6750 (-51B), dealers are likely buying into this move as they're short gamma in breakout regime. The concentration of heavy negative GEX between 6750-6770 creates a dangerous amplification zone where dealer hedging will accelerate any directional move. Key level is holding above 6750 - a break back below triggers aggressive dealer buying support, while a push toward 6800 (max positive gamma) faces increasing dealer selling pressure.\n\nBottom line: expect wild swings between 6750-6800 with dealers amplifying every move.",
